null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Explicit BOOTSTRAP_TOKEN env wins. If unset and api_tokens is empty on boot, auto-generate one and log it once with a clear delimiter; also write to UPLOAD_DIR/.bootstrap-token for one-shot retrieval."}, {"id": "phases_ts_codegen", "label": "TypeScript Client Codegen (api.types.ts)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 29", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "client/src/lib/api.types.ts generated from openapi.yaml and committed for diff visibility on PRs. Regenerated explicitly, not at build time."}, {"id": "phases_seed_users", "label": "Canonical Seed Users", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 36", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "phases_kanban_board", "label": "Kanban Board (pragmatic-drag-and-drop)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 165", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Atlassian's pragmatic-drag-and-drop chosen: framework-agnostic + keyboard-accessible. The Linear library."}, {"id": "phases_command_palette", "label": "Command Palette (Ctrl+K)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 192", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "phases_search_dsl", "label": "Search-as-DSL Filter Syntax", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 194", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Inline tokens parsed out of search field (assignee=magos status=in_progress,blocked type=bug urgent). Lets keyboard-first users skip chip toggles."}, {"id": "phases_echarts", "label": "Apache ECharts via vue-echarts", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 229", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "ECharts now; may roll custom later if visual polish demands it."}, {"id": "phases_cumulative_flow", "label": "Cumulative Flow Diagram (CFD) Endpoint", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 228", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "CFD endpoint cap is 50,000 events vs 5,000 for other stats endpoints since CFD must scan full project history. Split out as 3.0b because per-bucket category replay is ~half the work."}, {"id": "phases_cycle_time", "label": "Cycle Time (in_progress only, blocked excluded)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 256", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Blocked time is its own future metric. For personal use, cycle time counts in_progress only, not blocked. Companies tracking SLAs would care about blocked time separately."}, {"id": "phases_notifications", "label": "Notifications / @mentions System", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 231", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "phases_playwright_e2e", "label": "Playwright E2E Test Suite", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 243", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "phases_container_split", "label": "Two-Container Split (Backend API + Frontend Static)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 234", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "No nginx/Caddy: switchyard is tailnet-only with a single human + agents. A ~50-line Bun script handles static + SPA fallback + same-origin passthrough. Backend keeps service name 'switchyard' so existing agent URLs continue to work. Independent rebuild + concern separation."}, {"id": "phases_automation_rules", "label": "Native Automation Rules Engine", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 342", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Replaces n8n for simple if-status=X-do-Y rules. n8n keeps complex flows. Rules schema with trigger_event, conditions JSONB, actions JSONB."}, {"id": "phases_status_categories", "label": "Status Categories (backlog|planning|in_progress|blocked|closed)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 375", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Planning is first-class because the imperium-loop pipeline treats plan-generation and build-time as separate phases \u2014 collapsing them poisons cycle-time charts."}, {"id": "phases_resolution_field", "label": "Resolution Field (done|released|cancelled)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 376", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Separate field required when category=closed. Splits 'work complete' (done) from 'shipped' (released) from 'abandoned' (cancelled) without exploding categories."}, {"id": "phases_ticket_id_format", "label": "Ticket ID Format (KEY-NUMBER)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 379", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Human-readable in commits/PRs/n8n flows. Project key immutable after creation. UUIDs as canonical IDs underneath."}, {"id": "phases_epic_hierarchy", "label": "Epic Hierarchy (One Level Deep)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 380", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Epic \u2192 non-epic only, one level deep. Postgres trigger enforces the cross-row invariant. Future 'super epics' require trigger updates, not now."}, {"id": "phases_actor_model", "label": "Actor Model (users table with type=agent|human)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 381", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Cleaner than string actor IDs; every API token belongs to a user; audit log shows which agent acted."}, {"id": "phases_filesystem_attachments", "label": "Filesystem Attachment Storage (/data/uploads)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 385", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Homelab-appropriate. Adapter pattern allows S3 swap if constraints change."}, {"id": "phases_imperium_loop_migration", "label": "Imperium-Loop Migration Plan (cogitation-patch)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 399", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "phases_saved_views", "label": "Saved Views (saved_views table)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 231", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "phases_bulk_operations", "label": "Bulk Operations (multi-select, bulk-edit)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 231", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "phases_phase0", "target": "phases_phase1", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "PHASES.md", "source_location": "line 17", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "phases_phase1", "target": "phases_phase2", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": 